    <p> Today we had a little more on the note. First we made the van ready to go and drove the few hundred meters to Scenic World because we had to leave the campsite until 10 a.m. </p>
    <p> First we went up to the Scenic World caf&eacute;. From there we had an incredibly great view of the Blue Mountains, which, by the way, are anything but blue, but rather shone in a full green. In some travel guides it stood that it should smell very strongly of eucalyptus. Why was easy to see. The forests under us seemed to be pure eucalyptus forests. Unfortunately, they were so dry that nothing spoiled our noses from the wonderful fragrance. </p>
    <p> After taking some photos, we decided to take the first cable car down the mountain to go a little hiking down there. Below in the valley it was easy to find all the ways marked and consisted of wooden boards. Railings on the left and right and almost all paths were part of a large tour. Thus course -proof. </p>
    <p> With us there were certainly 50 or 60 Asians in the gondola. When we arrived at the bottom we waited briefly in the crowd to see in which direction the tour groups would move. We were lucky and everyone ran in the same direction. Of course we took the opposite direction. </p>
