    <p> The paths were very well maintained and it was nice and relaxed to walk through such a unique nature. Due to the dense tree tops, the temperatures remained in normal areas. Unfortunately, when we checked the first photos of the day, we had to find out that a fat lint is sitting in the middle of all photos. Unfortunately, this seemed to have come between the lenses somehow and that with a brand new camera. Of course, that pressed our mood a little. I spontaneously think of that in the city center of Sydney there is a Sony store and that it can definitely help us. </p>
    <p> Nevertheless, we tried not to let the day spoil ourselves and after some walking around the forest, we found a side course that brought us to the foot of the Katoomba waterfall on the foot of the Katoomba waterfall. Due to the lack of rain, this was only a trickle. But a fairly big iguana, or whatever he is, crossed our way. Since this cute mini dragon was also a camera horn, we got a few really good photos of him, despite the lint on the lens. </p>
    <p> Once again, we took the second gondola to the other side of the gorge. This gondola drove past the Katoomba waterfall and gave a great view over the mountains. On the other hand, only briefly decided to take some photos and drive back. After all, we had more plans. </p>
