    <p> Back in Sydney, we desperately searched for a quiet parking lot. Unfortunately we only found one on an extremely loud road. So we spontaneously decided to stop by in my old apartment and, if there was a place there, to spend the night there. Said done. Everything worked thanks to the help of the friendly roommate Adrian, who let us in. We quickly grabbed the most necessary things and moved back to my old room for the night. </p>
    <p> In the evening I went to the beautiful but a little short fireworks in the Darling Harbor with Steffi. Again, some really good photos were taken. Then we met Adrian for dinner in a restaurant in Chinatown. First we wanted to go a cocktail afterwards, but somehow we were too fun and went to bed. Unfortunately there was no really thought of sleeping because the couple in the next room, well, had their own fireworks. </p>
